Title: Partner
Company Location: 901 N 5th St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, United States
Company Description:
Unpretentious Fresh Vegan World Cuisine in a Deliciously Positive & Creative Environment!

Aside of Heart is a local facet of the Downtown Phoenix Arts District. As the only vegan restaurant in the area we fill the needs of the locals by providing deliciously healthy fare at a reasonable price. We have a menu that is constantly evolving. Aside of Heart offers classic favorites while also introducing new options that help customers explore their palates.

We support the community by opening our space up to local artists and educators. Our outdoor stage is a venue for many events, including an anti-poetry slam, theatre performances and shows by local bands. The interior of the restaurant is a gallery space. We showcase local artists and make available unique, hand crafted items created by Phoenix artisans.

Surrounded by street art and kitschy boutiques, our location on Roosevelt Row is a dining destination. Aside of Heart is a convenient place to grab a smoothie or snack during First Friday. Our inviting atmosphere makes for an enjoyable place to share a yummy vegan meal with a friend. Come by to discover your new favorite spot.

Title: Owner
Company Location: 2270 East Williams Field Road Suite 114, Gilbert, AZ 85295, United States
Company Description:
Caketini is an award winning family owned bakery started in Gilbert, AZ. Owner Cathy Monoscalco is a 5th Generation Arizona resident and a 3rd Generation Baker in her family. Cathy and her husband Mike have since opened up a 2nd and 3rd location in Scottsdale.

Caketini has quickly become part of an elite group of bakers here in Arizona by recently winning best bakery in Gilbert and best dessert at the Scottsdale Culinary Festival. 

Cathy and Mike pride themselves with the ability to work with locally owned businesses for sustainability and to add that unique Arizona flair. Each and every one of our desserts are formulated from family recipes or made from scratch. 

Customer service is key in establishing a healthy and strong relationships with our clients in going above and beyond to meet their unique needs. Caketini prides itself in not only providing outstanding desserts but great service in enhancing the overall customer experience.

Company Description:
Brother John’s Beer, Bourbon & BBQ
Located in the downtown corridor along Stone Avenue in Tucson, Arizona, is a fun, family‐friendly and unique destination restaurant as the first Bavarian‐inspired beer garden, bourbon bar and barbecue concepts in Arizona. Customers receive a comfort food dining experience with a selection of true slow‐smoked meats, southern‐style sides with a southwestern kick, salads and desserts, all containing thoughtfully local sourced ingredients. In addition to offering classes, tastings and regular food and beverage parings, Brother John’s also hosts a weekly live music series catering to all demographics.

TRUE SOUTHERN-STYLE BBQ
Brother John’s invites you for lunch, social hour, dinner and late night happy hour! We offer authentic slow pit-smoked barbecue meats and comfort food prepared on-site daily, fusing traditional southern-style barbecue with southwestern and Latin flavors, including incorporating a selection of regional chili peppers. The pit master slow smokes the highest quality meats in-house over Hickory, Applewood and Mesquite for up to 16 hours. If there is a pink ring around your meat, don’t fret. Title: Head Chef
Company Location: 1435 E University Dr #12, Tempe, AZ 85281, United States
Company Description:
Salut Kitchen Bar was named Best Wine Bar in Tempe, Arizona. It offers a wide array of flavorful and innovative menu items inspired by a mix of Mediterranean and American cuisine. The 3,400 square foot restaurant and bar, located between the infamous Mill Avenue and Tempe Marketplace, offers sophisticated-yet-affordable authentic food such as bruschetta, gourmet tapas, salads, sandwiches, entrees and an extensive wine selection that suits anyone looking for a memorable wine-and-dine experience.

Salut’s signature menu includes Hummus Nachos, Quinoa Fritters, and Pistachio Crusted Salmon. Enjoy these dishes along with other specialties for lunch and dinner every day and night of the week. Guests can also enjoy more than 100 types of wine by the glass and bottle. Salut features indoor and outdoor seating, a 20-seat bar, rustic and vintage décor, a wine room on display, a custom glass garage door that allows walking access to the 1,250 square foot dog-friendly patio, private event space, and more. It offers something for everyone in a relaxed European inspired environment

Title: Team Lead
Company Location: 9311 East Vía De Ventura, Scottsdale, AZ 60615, United States
Company Description:
TacoTime is a quick-service restaurant chain offering a tasty variety of freshly-prepared, home style, Mexican fare. No one takes more pride in the food they serve than we do at TacoTime. From humble beginnings in Eugene, Oregon back in 1960, the TacoTime Restaurant Chain has risen to dominate its position today as the quality leader in the Mexican quick-service restaurant franchise industry with 350+ locations in the United States, Canada and Kuwait.

Our ingredients and the care we take in making your food fresh make us truly a one-of-a-kind affordable taste experience. Where other fast food Mexican restaurants cut corners, we take the time to do it right. That’s the deliciously real, deliciously fresh difference at TacoTime. A difference you can taste in everything we make, from our world-famous hand-rolled Crisp Burritos to our unbeatable Mexi-Fries® that we cook to order. TacoTime's products are made with the freshest, most wholesome ingredients available. Menu items offer guests a real choice, from vegetarian items to a unique Chicken BLT Burrito.

Title: Sr. Director
Company Location: 9311 East via De Ventura, Scottsdale, AZ, United States
Company Description: With a collection of nearly 30 unique restaurant concepts, approximately 3,300 locations in roughly 30 countries and hundreds of signature recipes, Kahala Brands is one of the fastest growing franchising companies in the world. Generating over $1 billion in system-wide sales annually, Kahala Brands continues to grow and leaves a lasting footprint in each market that it enters. With dedicated and passionate in-house teams to support the brands from Marketing to Research & Development to Operations, Kahala Brands is extremely dedicated to helping franchisees achieve their entrepreneurial goals of building and operating their own business. We are Kahala Brands, where franchisees are in business for themselves but not by themselves.

Title: Shift Lead
Company Location: 9311 E via De Ventura Ste 102, Scottsdale, AZ 85258, United States
Company Description:
Since 1964, Blimpie® has been making fresh, wholesome subs that are good for you, your family and friends. Over 45 years we haven’t changed what’s important. We’ve held true to those beliefs and we are confident in what we do. Whatever comes next, you can count on Blimpie® to be right there, too – that’s why we are America’s Sub Shop.

To hear more about how Blimpie was started in Hoboken, New Jersey in 1964 visit our website: http://www.blimpie.com/about/the_blimpie_story.html

Title: Director of Sales & Marketing
Company Location: 2740 S Alma School Rd, Mesa, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Our passion is to combine delicious seafood with your family and friends in a fun, sometimes loud, and always very casual environment. We love groups both big and small and celebrations of every kind. Come dressed as you are, just don’t come alone. Be ready to bib up and dig into some good eatin’ . Best of all, we clean it all up after you depart. 

When guests eat at any Angry Crab Shack, they become part of our extended family. Just like family, every visit to an Angry Crab Shack makes memories no one wants to forget. That’s why we encourage guests to grab a pen and ‘tag’ the wall panels when memories are made. From anniversaries to birthdays to ‘We are pregnant’, you will see events of a lifetime celebrated on the walls at Angry Crab Shack. We are honored to share a memory with you so grab a pen and ‘tag’ a wall. (Just don’t say anything crabby).

Title: Head Hostess
Company Location: 4925 N 40th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
At North, we believe that there is so much in life to savor. North is about indulging in not just what we taste, but what we feel when we’re sharing a delicious handmade meal together. From the warmth that draws you in to our doors, to the anticipation that floods your senses as you settle in, to the vibrant energy that lets you know you’re in for something special, every detail of the North experience is meant to connect us with one another and satisfy. 

We’re looking for managers, servers, chefs, bussers and bartenders to join our team and help give our guests moments, bites and sips worth savoring. Bring your talent to a warm and welcoming environment, where it will be nurtured and rewarded. There’s always room for passionate and dedicated people at our table.

Title: Business Owner
Company Location: 725 S Rural Rd Ste 120, Tempe, AZ 85281, United States
Company Description:
Yogurtini self-serve, founded in 2008, strives to bring you only the finest frozen yogurts and toppings. With classic frozen yogurt flavors such as vanilla and cheesecake, and new favorites like mango, Acai, and lychee, we want your tastebuds to be continually excited. That’s why you can find our extensive list of frozen yogurts rotating regularly, to feature 16 flavors in-store.

Mix in as many toppings as you like, choosing from over 75 that we have available at our exclusive topping bar. We have everything you could dream of, including granola, fresh fruits, all your favorite candies and cereals, and specialty items including espresso beans, and even Sriracha hot sauce.

At Yogurtini, we believe that no taste should be overlooked. That’s why we’ve provided you with so many options. It’s all there in front of you, the rest is up to you.

Yogurtini is a fast growing company and offers franchising opportunities. There are currently 9 nationwide locations and is projected to grow to 50 stores by early 2012. www.yogurtini.com

Title: Lead Bartender
Company Location: 1340 E 8th Street Ste 104, Tempe, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Our History…

With the opening of our Tempe brewpub in 1996, we began our venture into the restaurant and brewing industry in Tempe, Arizona.  The Four Peaks Brewing Company is credited with restoring our historic original location which once held the old Borden’s Creamery and Ice House, one of Tempe’s oldest brick buildings.  Located East of Arizona State University on 8th Street, this beautiful turn of the century warehouse is now listed with the National Historical Society.  Originally constructed in 1892, it has had a number of additions and renovations through 1927.  Since then the building has not changed its Mission Revival style architecture and still sets the mood for the Brewery’s atmosphere.  The structure is constructed almost entirely of red brick, with wooden ceilings and a glass parapet reaching as high as 35 feet, the ceiling is supported by original Carnegie steel framework.

Who picks a 100 year old building to house a restaurant and brewery?  Co-founders, Jim Scussel, Andrew Ingram, Randy Schultz, and Arthur Craft all had an important role in making us who we are today.  

Through our efforts the Four Peaks Brewing Company has grown into Arizona’s Largest Microbrewery with over 4000 draft, bottle and can accounts state wide in local bars, restaurants and retail stores. You can find a Four Peaks beer about anywhere in the state. We opened our first satellite location, Four Peaks Grill & Tap in North Scottsdale in January 2004, our Wilson Tasting Room and Distribution Center in Tempe in 2012 and our new Sky Harbor Airport location in the fall of 2013. In December 2015, we announced new ownership and are proud to be a part of the High End section of the Anheuser-Busch.

Today the company continues to move forward in its growth while retaining our original goals – providing great craft beer, high quality food and friendly, consistent, knowledgeable service.

Title: Director of People Services
Company Location: 6263 North Scottsdale Road, Scottsdale, AZ 85250, United States
Company Description:
Most people think of the “Aloha Spirit” as Hawaii’s welcoming attitude. In the Hawaiian language, “aloha” has an even deeper meaning. In addition to “hello,” “goodbye,” and “love,” it means “the joyful (oha) sharing (alo) of life energy (ha) in the present (alo).” This is the spirit our team strives to embody every day, whether we are at a restaurant on the islands or in the desert.

Founder Randy Schoch felt the Aloha Spirit the moment he became the General Manager at Nick’s Fishmarket in Hawaii at the age of 23. He was fueled by a passion for going above and beyond, and ended up purchasing the restaurant within five years. After opening the chic Black Orchid restaurant and nightclub in Honolulu, Randy acquired the Ruth’s Chris Steak House franchise in Hawaii and began his journey into franchising. 

In 1995, Randy moved to the mainland and established Desert Island Restaurants. Although the desert was his new home, his connection with the islands stayed strong. Since then, Randy has opened six Ruth’s Chris Steak Houses and two Romano’s Macaroni Grill locations in Hawaii. Inspired by the islands’ melting pot of Asian and American influences, he also introduced Roy’s® to Arizona and California, opened Thaifoon — Taste of Asia®, and launched the Ling & Louie’s Bar and Grill concept, which has grown to 4 locations across the country. 

The storied success of the Ruth’s Chris Hawaii locations lead Ruth’s Hospitality Group, Inc. – parent company of Ruth’s Chris Steak House – to acquire the six restaurants from Desert Island in late 2017. “With RHGI’s leadership and strength of the Ruth’s Chris Steak House brand, the future of these locations is in excellent hands,” said Schoch. “I’m confident that RHGI will build upon our accomplishments and embrace the island spirit that has continuously guided everything our team members do.” 

No matter how far we grow, or which desert or island our next restaurant calls home, we will always be rooted in the Aloha Spirit.

Title: Partner
Company Location: 230 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Liberty Market is an unpretentious urban bistro, located in the heart of Old Town Gilbert. The restaurant itself was opened in 2009 by partners Joe & Cindy Johnston and David & Kiersten Traina, quickly becoming a popular eating & meeting place in the East Valley. The building itself has been in existence since the early 1930′s serving Gilbert as a grocery store. Ben Ong, a Chinese immigrant, began working at the store in 1936 and then purchased the store with his wife Mae Ong in 1943. The Ongs modernized and doubled the stores size in 1958, and then operated it until 1981 when they sold it to Sam & Mary Bromert. Even in 1981 Gilbert had only 6,000 residents and there wasn’t another grocery store within 15 miles. Joe Johnston and his brothers bought the market in 2006 from the Bromerts.

Today Liberty Market is an award winning, Zagat rated restaurant serving a diverse and refined menu featuring wood fired pizza, sandwiches, salads, burgers, pasta,  gourmet style entrees, house-made desserts and features a premium espresso bar and diverse beer+wine list. Liberty Market serves Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner 7 days a week and has become a favorite meeting and eating place for families, friends and business people alike. Even the one-of-a-kind bathrooms have one awards!

General Manager William Johnston

Title: Entrepreneur
Company Location: 230 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Liberty Market is an unpretentious urban bistro, located in the heart of Old Town Gilbert. The restaurant itself was opened in 2009 by partners Joe & Cindy Johnston and David & Kiersten Traina, quickly becoming a popular eating & meeting place in the East Valley. The building itself has been in existence since the early 1930′s serving Gilbert as a grocery store. Ben Ong, a Chinese immigrant, began working at the store in 1936 and then purchased the store with his wife Mae Ong in 1943. The Ongs modernized and doubled the stores size in 1958, and then operated it until 1981 when they sold it to Sam & Mary Bromert. Even in 1981 Gilbert had only 6,000 residents and there wasn’t another grocery store within 15 miles. Joe Johnston and his brothers bought the market in 2006 from the Bromerts.

Today Liberty Market is an award winning, Zagat rated restaurant serving a diverse and refined menu featuring wood fired pizza, sandwiches, salads, burgers, pasta,  gourmet style entrees, house-made desserts and features a premium espresso bar and diverse beer+wine list. Liberty Market serves Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner 7 days a week and has become a favorite meeting and eating place for families, friends and business people alike. Even the one-of-a-kind bathrooms have one awards!

General Manager William Johnston

Title: VP of Engineering
Company Location: 743 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85234, United States
Company Description:
Salad and Go is a gourmet salad drive-thru restaurant chain located throughout the Phoenix Valley, founded with a mission to make ready-to-eat food available and affordable to everyone, not just the few. Did you know that 70% of all eating out consumption happens at a fast food restaurant? It’s not hard to understand why this is; traditional drive-thru fast food is convenient, inexpensive and filling. But what if we could make it just as convenient and affordable to eat fresh, great tasting, good-for-you food? It is this very notion that drives us. We believe if we can bring healthy, great tasting food to a drive-thru with fast food speed and prices, we can help change the health of America.

When developing Salad and Go, we started with taste. Our world-class salads are made using only the freshest and finest ingredients, from our house-made dressings to our freshly chopped vegetables and cooked in-house meats. Using whole, natural and organic ingredients, we are proud to offer food that not only tastes great, but also is good for you!

It started with a question, “Why can’t we just get something fresh and healthy through a drive-thru that tastes great too?” And now there is an answer. It’s time to feel good about fast food.

Title: Head Bartender
Company Location: 800 East 16th Street, Tucson, AZ 85719, United States
Company Description:
Barrio Brewing Co. found its first home in 1991 at a little restaurant near the University of Arizona campus popularly known as Gentle Ben’s. When Dennis and Tauna took ownership of the property it was called “Dirtbags West,” though the Arnolds quickly reinstated the original name of the location (circa 1971) and added “Brewing Company” to the title. They installed fermentation tanks and started their entire operation with three ales — the Tucson Blonde, Red Cat Amber, and Copperhead Pale Ale — all of which are still brewed today, though they’ve also added a number of other styles to that repertoire, including three specialty craft beers named for each of their three children. When brewing operations outgrew their rojooriginal home at Gentle Ben’s in 2006, the Arnold’s relocated to a former WWII quonset-hut-turned-warehouse about two miles south near Downtown Tucson, which they dubbed “Barrio”. Today, the offerings of Barrio Brewing Co. include two Great American Beer Fest Medal Winners (Bronze for the Barrio Rojo in 2015 & Gold for Nolan’s Porter in 2008) as well as the longest continually-brewed beer in the State of Arizona—the Barrio Blonde. Now Barrio Blonde, Rojo,
and Blanco cans can be found in markets across the state of Arizona, and the entire catalog can be sampled on draft from Tucson to Flagstaff.

Cheers to you, and to good locally-brewed craft beer!

Title: CFO
Company Location: 743 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85234, United States
Company Description:
Salad and Go is a gourmet salad drive-thru restaurant chain located throughout the Phoenix Valley, founded with a mission to make ready-to-eat food available and affordable to everyone, not just the few. Did you know that 70% of all eating out consumption happens at a fast food restaurant? It’s not hard to understand why this is; traditional drive-thru fast food is convenient, inexpensive and filling. But what if we could make it just as convenient and affordable to eat fresh, great tasting, good-for-you food? It is this very notion that drives us. We believe if we can bring healthy, great tasting food to a drive-thru with fast food speed and prices, we can help change the health of America.

When developing Salad and Go, we started with taste. Our world-class salads are made using only the freshest and finest ingredients, from our house-made dressings to our freshly chopped vegetables and cooked in-house meats. Using whole, natural and organic ingredients, we are proud to offer food that not only tastes great, but also is good for you!

It started with a question, “Why can’t we just get something fresh and healthy through a drive-thru that tastes great too?” And now there is an answer. It’s time to feel good about fast food.

Title: Regional Director Sales & Marketing
Company Location: 6263 North Scottsdale Road, Scottsdale, AZ 85250, United States
Company Description:
Most people think of the “Aloha Spirit” as Hawaii’s welcoming attitude. In the Hawaiian language, “aloha” has an even deeper meaning. In addition to “hello,” “goodbye,” and “love,” it means “the joyful (oha) sharing (alo) of life energy (ha) in the present (alo).” This is the spirit our team strives to embody every day, whether we are at a restaurant on the islands or in the desert.

Founder Randy Schoch felt the Aloha Spirit the moment he became the General Manager at Nick’s Fishmarket in Hawaii at the age of 23. He was fueled by a passion for going above and beyond, and ended up purchasing the restaurant within five years. After opening the chic Black Orchid restaurant and nightclub in Honolulu, Randy acquired the Ruth’s Chris Steak House franchise in Hawaii and began his journey into franchising. 

In 1995, Randy moved to the mainland and established Desert Island Restaurants. Although the desert was his new home, his connection with the islands stayed strong. Since then, Randy has opened six Ruth’s Chris Steak Houses and two Romano’s Macaroni Grill locations in Hawaii. Inspired by the islands’ melting pot of Asian and American influences, he also introduced Roy’s® to Arizona and California, opened Thaifoon — Taste of Asia®, and launched the Ling & Louie’s Bar and Grill concept, which has grown to 4 locations across the country. 

The storied success of the Ruth’s Chris Hawaii locations lead Ruth’s Hospitality Group, Inc. – parent company of Ruth’s Chris Steak House – to acquire the six restaurants from Desert Island in late 2017. “With RHGI’s leadership and strength of the Ruth’s Chris Steak House brand, the future of these locations is in excellent hands,” said Schoch. “I’m confident that RHGI will build upon our accomplishments and embrace the island spirit that has continuously guided everything our team members do.” 

No matter how far we grow, or which desert or island our next restaurant calls home, we will always be rooted in the Aloha Spirit.

Title: Head Bartender
Contact Location: California, san diego county, United States
Company Location: 800 East 16th Street, Tucson, AZ 85719, United States
Company Description:
Barrio Brewing Co. found its first home in 1991 at a little restaurant near the University of Arizona campus popularly known as Gentle Ben’s. When Dennis and Tauna took ownership of the property it was called “Dirtbags West,” though the Arnolds quickly reinstated the original name of the location (circa 1971) and added “Brewing Company” to the title. They installed fermentation tanks and started their entire operation with three ales — the Tucson Blonde, Red Cat Amber, and Copperhead Pale Ale — all of which are still brewed today, though they’ve also added a number of other styles to that repertoire, including three specialty craft beers named for each of their three children. When brewing operations outgrew their rojooriginal home at Gentle Ben’s in 2006, the Arnold’s relocated to a former WWII quonset-hut-turned-warehouse about two miles south near Downtown Tucson, which they dubbed “Barrio”. Today, the offerings of Barrio Brewing Co. include two Great American Beer Fest Medal Winners (Bronze for the Barrio Rojo in 2015 & Gold for Nolan’s Porter in 2008) as well as the longest continually-brewed beer in the State of Arizona—the Barrio Blonde. Now Barrio Blonde, Rojo,
and Blanco cans can be found in markets across the state of Arizona, and the entire catalog can be sampled on draft from Tucson to Flagstaff.

Cheers to you, and to good locally-brewed craft beer!

Title: Co Owner
Company Location: 100 South Avenida Del Convento Ste 150, Tucson, AZ 85745, United States
Company Description:
New American Kitchen with focuses on local farms and craft cocktails.

See our Chefs Bio Below:

At just 28 years of age, Chef Ryan Clark has accomplished much in his 
career. The Tucson native is true to his roots, committed to using local, 
sustainably produced ingredients, his dishes reflect the freshness and 
unique flavors that can only result from this kind of culinary sensibility.
From the minute he went to work as a Sous Chef at Fuego Restaurant in 
Tucson in 1999, Clark knew he wanted to be a chef. Graduating at the 
top of his class and on the Dean's List from the Culinary Institute of 
America, in Hyde Park, New York, he garnered his received his first 
accolade of 23 when he was named one of the Top Sixteen Junior Chefs 
in the US by the American Culinary Foundation.
After working for a few years in NY, Clark came "home" to Arizona, 
working at Elements Restaurant at the Sanctuary Resort in Paradise 
Valley under acclaimed Chef Beau MacMillan before making his way 
back to Tucson where he honed his craft at the world renowned Canyon 
Ranch Resort & Spa and at The Dish Bistro. He earned and held his first 
Executive Chef position at the Lodge on the Desert until October of 2013 
when he had the opportunity to partner in his own restaurant, Agustin 
Kitchen, at Mercado San Agustin.
Chef Clark holds the rare distinction of being Tucson's Iron Chef for three 
consecutive years, he also holds the title of Tucson's Copper Chef, and he 
has won top honors twice in the World Margarita Challenge for his 
innovative creations. In 2012, he was nominated by Food and Wine 
Magazine as one of the top 10 Best New Chef in the Southwest. He is 
currently Vice Chair of the Southern Arizona chapter of Slow Food. 
Clark's first cookbook "Modern Southwest Cooking" released in 
October, 2013, showcases innovative recipes that combine his passion 
for regional cooking and local ingredients.

Title: Chief Operating Officer
Company Location: 800 East 16th Street, Tucson, AZ 85719, United States
Company Description:
Barrio Brewing Co. found its first home in 1991 at a little restaurant near the University of Arizona campus popularly known as Gentle Ben’s. When Dennis and Tauna took ownership of the property it was called “Dirtbags West,” though the Arnolds quickly reinstated the original name of the location (circa 1971) and added “Brewing Company” to the title. They installed fermentation tanks and started their entire operation with three ales — the Tucson Blonde, Red Cat Amber, and Copperhead Pale Ale — all of which are still brewed today, though they’ve also added a number of other styles to that repertoire, including three specialty craft beers named for each of their three children. When brewing operations outgrew their rojooriginal home at Gentle Ben’s in 2006, the Arnold’s relocated to a former WWII quonset-hut-turned-warehouse about two miles south near Downtown Tucson, which they dubbed “Barrio”. Today, the offerings of Barrio Brewing Co. include two Great American Beer Fest Medal Winners (Bronze for the Barrio Rojo in 2015 & Gold for Nolan’s Porter in 2008) as well as the longest continually-brewed beer in the State of Arizona—the Barrio Blonde. Now Barrio Blonde, Rojo,
and Blanco cans can be found in markets across the state of Arizona, and the entire catalog can be sampled on draft from Tucson to Flagstaff.

Cheers to you, and to good locally-brewed craft beer!

Title: CEO
Company Location: 743 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85234, United States
Company Description:
Salad and Go is a gourmet salad drive-thru restaurant chain located throughout the Phoenix Valley, founded with a mission to make ready-to-eat food available and affordable to everyone, not just the few. Did you know that 70% of all eating out consumption happens at a fast food restaurant? It’s not hard to understand why this is; traditional drive-thru fast food is convenient, inexpensive and filling. But what if we could make it just as convenient and affordable to eat fresh, great tasting, good-for-you food? It is this very notion that drives us. We believe if we can bring healthy, great tasting food to a drive-thru with fast food speed and prices, we can help change the health of America.

When developing Salad and Go, we started with taste. Our world-class salads are made using only the freshest and finest ingredients, from our house-made dressings to our freshly chopped vegetables and cooked in-house meats. Using whole, natural and organic ingredients, we are proud to offer food that not only tastes great, but also is good for you!

It started with a question, “Why can’t we just get something fresh and healthy through a drive-thru that tastes great too?” And now there is an answer. It’s time to feel good about fast food.

Title: Owner
Company Location: 4166 N Scottsdale Rd #102, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, United States
Company Description:
Second Story Liquor Bar was born of an idea that providing amazing cocktails and a thoughtful menu in a stylish environment should not be an anomaly in Old Town Scottsdale. The journey a guest undertakes anytime they visit SSLB will be relevant and unique each time they walk up the stairs. There should be a definite feeling of relief that the daily grind towards mediocrity and mass production has stopped when a guest enters the cool confines of our property.

The team at SSLB is committed to providing the best experience to our guests, expecting the best from ourselves and challenging each other to keep learning. This daily commitment to excellence is a part of our culture that includes our own love of dining, drinking and 
traveling to augment our knowledge base and to make SSLB one of the premier restaurant destinations in the Southwest. 

Each day is a blank canvas for us here at SSLB and the canvas is ever changing to include our dreams and desires of an oasis in the desert. Each and every guest is invited along on this journey. SSLB is a sensory and tactile story that engages foodie and novice alike.  An elegant dram of whiskey paired with a savory bite, thoughtfully prepared and served by a caring staff, is our prologue and the story continues on from there. 

Fresh ingredients and fine whiskeys are the backbone of the Second Story’s concept; an experience designed for our guests to offer an inside look at the art of culinary and perfectly crafted cocktails.  
 
You are in safe hands...relax...enjoy yourself.  Forget about tomorrow.   It’s just about you and this moment we cross paths. Allow your palette to enjoy the finer side of crafted food and spirits.  

Welcome to the Second Story Liquor Bar

Tommy Plato | John Christie | JT Tillman | Nick Rusticus

Title: LEAD COOK

Company Description:

Title: Director of Pub Operations
Company Location: 1340 E 8th Street Ste 104, Tempe, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Our History…

With the opening of our Tempe brewpub in 1996, we began our venture into the restaurant and brewing industry in Tempe, Arizona.  The Four Peaks Brewing Company is credited with restoring our historic original location which once held the old Borden’s Creamery and Ice House, one of Tempe’s oldest brick buildings.  Located East of Arizona State University on 8th Street, this beautiful turn of the century warehouse is now listed with the National Historical Society.  Originally constructed in 1892, it has had a number of additions and renovations through 1927.  Since then the building has not changed its Mission Revival style architecture and still sets the mood for the Brewery’s atmosphere.  The structure is constructed almost entirely of red brick, with wooden ceilings and a glass parapet reaching as high as 35 feet, the ceiling is supported by original Carnegie steel framework.

Who picks a 100 year old building to house a restaurant and brewery?  Co-founders, Jim Scussel, Andrew Ingram, Randy Schultz, and Arthur Craft all had an important role in making us who we are today.  

Through our efforts the Four Peaks Brewing Company has grown into Arizona’s Largest Microbrewery with over 4000 draft, bottle and can accounts state wide in local bars, restaurants and retail stores. You can find a Four Peaks beer about anywhere in the state. We opened our first satellite location, Four Peaks Grill & Tap in North Scottsdale in January 2004, our Wilson Tasting Room and Distribution Center in Tempe in 2012 and our new Sky Harbor Airport location in the fall of 2013. In December 2015, we announced new ownership and are proud to be a part of the High End section of the Anheuser-Busch.

Today the company continues to move forward in its growth while retaining our original goals – providing great craft beer, high quality food and friendly, consistent, knowledgeable service.

Title: Director of Technology Services
Company Location: 743 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85234, United States
Company Description:
Salad and Go is a gourmet salad drive-thru restaurant chain located throughout the Phoenix Valley, founded with a mission to make ready-to-eat food available and affordable to everyone, not just the few. Did you know that 70% of all eating out consumption happens at a fast food restaurant? It’s not hard to understand why this is; traditional drive-thru fast food is convenient, inexpensive and filling. But what if we could make it just as convenient and affordable to eat fresh, great tasting, good-for-you food? It is this very notion that drives us. We believe if we can bring healthy, great tasting food to a drive-thru with fast food speed and prices, we can help change the health of America.

When developing Salad and Go, we started with taste. Our world-class salads are made using only the freshest and finest ingredients, from our house-made dressings to our freshly chopped vegetables and cooked in-house meats. Using whole, natural and organic ingredients, we are proud to offer food that not only tastes great, but also is good for you!

It started with a question, “Why can’t we just get something fresh and healthy through a drive-thru that tastes great too?” And now there is an answer. It’s time to feel good about fast food.

But what if we could make it just as convenient and affordable to eat fresh, great tasting, good-for-you food? It is this very notion that drives us. We believe if we can bring healthy, great tasting food to a drive-thru with fast food speed and prices, we can help change the health of America.

When developing Salad and Go, we started with taste. Our world-class salads are made using only the freshest and finest ingredients, from our house-made dressings to our freshly chopped vegetables and cooked in-house meats. Using whole, natural and organic ingredients, we are proud to offer food that not only tastes great, but also is good for you!

It started with a question, “Why can’t we just get something fresh and healthy through a drive-thru that tastes great too?” And now there is an answer. It’s time to feel good about fast food.

Title: Director of Performance
Company Location: 1340 E 8th Street Ste 104, Tempe, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Our History…

With the opening of our Tempe brewpub in 1996, we began our venture into the restaurant and brewing industry in Tempe, Arizona.  The Four Peaks Brewing Company is credited with restoring our historic original location which once held the old Borden’s Creamery and Ice House, one of Tempe’s oldest brick buildings.  Located East of Arizona State University on 8th Street, this beautiful turn of the century warehouse is now listed with the National Historical Society.  Originally constructed in 1892, it has had a number of additions and renovations through 1927.  Since then the building has not changed its Mission Revival style architecture and still sets the mood for the Brewery’s atmosphere.  The structure is constructed almost entirely of red brick, with wooden ceilings and a glass parapet reaching as high as 35 feet, the ceiling is supported by original Carnegie steel framework.

Who picks a 100 year old building to house a restaurant and brewery?  Co-founders, Jim Scussel, Andrew Ingram, Randy Schultz, and Arthur Craft all had an important role in making us who we are today.  

Through our efforts the Four Peaks Brewing Company has grown into Arizona’s Largest Microbrewery with over 4000 draft, bottle and can accounts state wide in local bars, restaurants and retail stores. You can find a Four Peaks beer about anywhere in the state. We opened our first satellite location, Four Peaks Grill & Tap in North Scottsdale in January 2004, our Wilson Tasting Room and Distribution Center in Tempe in 2012 and our new Sky Harbor Airport location in the fall of 2013. In December 2015, we announced new ownership and are proud to be a part of the High End section of the Anheuser-Busch.

Today the company continues to move forward in its growth while retaining our original goals – providing great craft beer, high quality food and friendly, consistent, knowledgeable service.

Title: Beverage Director/Marketing and Community Relations
Company Location: 2740 S Alma School Rd, Mesa, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Our passion is to combine delicious seafood with your family and friends in a fun, sometimes loud, and always very casual environment. We love groups both big and small and celebrations of every kind. Come dressed as you are, just don’t come alone. Be ready to bib up and dig into some good eatin’ . Best of all, we clean it all up after you depart. 

When guests eat at any Angry Crab Shack, they become part of our extended family. Just like family, every visit to an Angry Crab Shack makes memories no one wants to forget. That’s why we encourage guests to grab a pen and ‘tag’ the wall panels when memories are made. From anniversaries to birthdays to ‘We are pregnant’, you will see events of a lifetime celebrated on the walls at Angry Crab Shack. We are honored to share a memory with you so grab a pen and ‘tag’ a wall. (Just don’t say anything crabby).

We love groups both big and small and celebrations of every kind. Come dressed as you are, just don’t come alone. Be ready to bib up and dig into some good eatin’ . Best of all, we clean it all up after you depart. 

When guests eat at any Angry Crab Shack, they become part of our extended family. Just like family, every visit to an Angry Crab Shack makes memories no one wants to forget. That’s why we encourage guests to grab a pen and ‘tag’ the wall panels when memories are made. From anniversaries to birthdays to ‘We are pregnant’, you will see events of a lifetime celebrated on the walls at Angry Crab Shack. We are honored to share a memory with you so grab a pen and ‘tag’ a wall. (Just don’t say anything crabby).

Conceived in 1995 in the arena of high-level event planning and creative cuisine.

The Herb Box is powered by founder-owner Susan Smederovac-Wilcox. Her approach can be summed up in three words: Innovative World Creations. Always on the look out for the new, Wilcox seems to be driven by the joy of daily epiphanies. Title: Owner / Operator BLIMPIE Subs and Salads

Since 1964, Blimpie® has been making fresh, wholesome subs that are good for you, your family and friends. Over 45 years we haven’t changed what’s important. Title: National Beverage Director
Company Location: 7299 N Scottsdale Rd, Scottsdale, AZ 85253, United States
Company Description:
Roka Akor Steak & Sushi serves modern Robatayaki Japanese cuisine cooked over bincho tan (oak charcoal) on the multi-tiered robata grill. Seating flanks the central feature of the dining room, the robata grill, for guests who want a front row seat. The menu offers small plates, warm bites, a variety of salads, sashimi, sushi, entrées consisting of Prime steaks, fish, chicken and vegetables from the grill, and desserts.

Select which Roka Akor you would like more information on from our "Products" section here or visit our website at www.RokaAkor.com where you will find menus, events, in the media and more. Don’t forget to subscribe to our newsletter to find out about exclusive offers!

Located in Scottsdale, AZ, San Francisco, CA (new!), Chicago, IL and Old Orchard, IL (new!), this is a dining experience to remember.

Title: Owner
Company Location: 2170 E Baseline Rd, Phoenix, AZ 85042-6950, United States
Company Description: Unlike many pizza franchises, RedBrick Pizza serves up both individual and family size pizzas so you will appeal to both large groups and the solo-dining lunch crowd. Our guest-focused approach doesn’t stop there, either. Our menu of build-your-own options and signature pizzas will ensure there’s a little something for everyone. RedBrick Pizza is also proud to offer gluten-free, vegetarian and vegan options. In addition to our fire-roasted gourmet pizzas, we also serve fresh salads and Fhazani®, a fire-roasted flatbread sandwich unique to RedBrick Pizza. Add in some authentic gelato, plus beer and wine where permitted, and you’ve got everything you need to offer your guests a fantastic dining experience.
